p:
Response curves based on climatic variables identified in provenance tests have already been investigated separately for different species (e.g., 
 Rehfeldt et al., 2002; 
 Mátyás & Nagy, 2005 for 
 P. sylvestris; 
 Horváth & Mátyás, 2016 for 
 Fagus sylvatica; 
 Sáenz-Romero et al., 2017 for 
 Q. petraea), but we used a novel comparative approach in this study. Interestingly, our results are consistent with those of the previous studies, in which drought-indicating variables, not unlike annual dryness index (e.g., Ellenberg drought index, 
 Horváth & Mátyás, 2016; summer drought period length, 
 Frank et al., 2017a) were found to be significant.
